reviews.review_text:
I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

After trudging through the very lackluster Phoenix, AZ, run that came before it, this show was refreshing. Much better energy in both sets I and II, with Jerry in fine form for a High Time, Scarlet>Fire, and good take on an up-tempo Dark Star. The Drums>Space goes some interesting places, but it is not as good as 3/5 (26 minutes of pure headiness), which is the standout thus far among the first shows of 1994 that I have listened to. Nice Miracle towards the end too, which almost launches into a Truckin' jam. Vince plays well throughout. I like his '94 selection of keys and vocals. SOTM goes out with a bang!
